</S>
<S ID="42072">
While the preview window is open, you can access most other ScanWorX windows.
</S>
<S ID="42244">
So, for example, if the image in the preview window was too dark or too light, or if the page is skewed, you can make adjustments and rescan the page before processing it.
</S>
<S ID="42351">
In addition, at the top of the preview window, you can access a number of commands to operate the system.
</S>
